main event: A civilian observer spotted approximately 12 lights arranged in a horizontal line, blinking on and off consecutively from one end to the other. The object was traveling at a high rate of speed, estimated around 400 mph, through the sky in Chicago, Illinois.
interesting points: The object's flight path varied, traveling west, then due south, then east, and finally north.
The object was estimated to be flying at an altitude of 500-800 feet.
The observer did not notice any sound coming from the object.
The sighting lasted for approximately 5-10 seconds.
The observer was an air passenger on a commercial airliner when they witnessed the event.
sighted object: approximately 12 blinking lights in a horizontal line
